section.section:
Effective for refunds issued after April 24, 2008, except for the provisions of KRS 138.351, 141.044(2), 141.235(3), and subsection (3) of this section, interest authorized under this subsection shall begin to accrue sixty (60) days after the latest of:
The due date of the return;
The date the return was filed;
The date the tax was paid;
The last day prescribed by law for filing the return; or
The date an amended return claiming a refund is filed.
